-- Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Ferreyros, Panoro, Rio Alto
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-04-27T20:29:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-27/peru-stocks-buenaventura-irl-rio-alto-telefonica.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Peru trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of market close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.5 percent to 22,908.98. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index climbed 1.3 percent to 2,979.24.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, rose 5.9 percent to 72 cents after copper
advanced in New York for a fourth day.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., climbed 2.1 percent to 3 soles. The shares
rose as U.S. stocks gained, said Arlen Lahura, a trader at
brokerage Coril SAB in Lima. Ferreyros is scheduled to report
first-quarter earnings after the market’s close today.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner, rose
for a third session, adding 2.9 percent to $4.31 after gold
advanced in  New York .  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, gained 1.8 percent to $42.25. The
company is scheduled to report first-quarter earnings after the
market’s close today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
